Exploration

Ben Weinstein

January 20, 2017

Seasonal patterns of dive depth

#dive depth and time
ggplot(dive,aes(x=timestamp,y=DepthMax)) + geom_point()  + scale_x_datetime(date_breaks = "2 week",date_labels = "%m/%d/%y") + scale_y_reverse() + theme_bw() + labs(x="Date")

ggsave("Figures/Depth_Time.jpg",height=5,width=5)

By individual

ggplot(dive,aes(x=timestamp,y=DepthMax)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth() + scale_x_datetime(date_breaks = "2 week") + scale_y_reverse() + facet_wrap(~Animal,scales="free")

ggsave("Figures/Depth_Time.jpg",height=5,width=5)

By Month

ggplot(dive,aes(x=timestamp,y=DepthMax,col=Month)) + geom_point()  + scale_y_reverse() + facet_wrap(~Animal,scales="free_x") + labs(col="Animal",x="Time") + scale_x_datetime(date_breaks = "2 week",date_labels = "%m/%d/%y")

#dive data and dutation, colored by month
ggplot(data=dive,aes(x=DurationMax, y=DepthMax,col=Month)) + geom_point() + theme_bw()

average depth over month

dive %>% group_by(Month) %>% summarize(mean(DepthMax))
## # A tibble: 6 × 2

Daily patterns of dive depth

#timestamp
ggplot(data=dive,aes(x=as.numeric(Hour),y=DepthMax)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth() + scale_y_reverse() + facet_wrap(~Month) + scale_x_continuous(breaks=seq(0,24,4))

per individual

ggplot(data=dive,aes(x=as.numeric(Hour),y=DepthMax)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth() + scale_y_reverse() + facet_wrap(Animal~Month) + scale_x_continuous(breaks=seq(0,24,4))
